{"type":"gap_analysis_final","model":"Gemma-2-2B","gap_ms":0.25,"gap_pct_tg2000":3.8,"gap_pct_tg100":12,"root_cause":"fixed_per_token_dispatch_overhead","launches_per_token":312,"estimated_us_per_launch":0.8,"graph_reuse":"not_faster_on_rocm71","swa_blocks_graph":true,"conclusion":"The 3.5% gap is a fixed ~0.25ms per-token host dispatch cost that cannot be eliminated on ROCm 7.1. hipGraph doesn't help. Reducing launch count is the only path, which the plan system would enable. For tg2000, the gap is small (3.8%) because attention dominates. For short sequences it's larger (12% at tg100)."}
