{"type":"finding","key":"baseline_dispatch_mechanism","detail":"Baseline uses AOT-compiled kernels with <<<>>> syntax (direct call). We use JIT .hsaco + hipModuleLaunchKernel (function pointer). The ~0.3ms fixed overhead is likely from: (1) hipModuleLaunchKernel vs direct <<<>>> dispatch overhead per launch, (2) JIT compiler producing slightly less optimized code than AOT. This is architectural to the JIT approach and cannot be eliminated without switching to AOT compilation."}
{"type":"finding","key":"baseline_no_graph_gemma2","detail":"Confirmed: baseline does NOT use graph reuse for Gemma-2 (SWA causes pointer changes that reset graph warmup). Both baseline and megakernel use direct per-token kernel launches for Gemma-2."}
